t','image/jpeg',0),(501,3,'2013-07-18 09:23:41','2013-07-18 13:23:41','','Family circus','','inherit','open','open','','family-circus','','','2013-07-18 09:23:41','2013-07-18 13:23:41','',0,'http://mrcornelius.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Family-circus.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(502,3,'2013-07-18 09:24:30','2013-07-18 13:24:30','','cup of tea','','inherit','open','open','','cup-of-tea','','','2013-07-18 09:24:30','2013-07-18 13:24:30','',0,'http://mrcornelius.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/cup-of-tea.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(503,3,'2013-07-18 09:25:00','2013-07-18 13:25:00','','M & M','','inherit','open','open','','m-m','','','2013-07-18 09:25:00','2013-07-18 13:25:00','',0,'http://mrcornelius.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/M-M.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(504,3,'2013-07-18 09:25:46','2013-07-18 13:25:46','','DSCN0503','','inherit','open','open','','dscn0503','','','2013-07-18 09:25:46','2013-07-18 13:25:46','',0,'http://mrcornelius.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/DSCN0503.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(505,3,'2013-07-18 09:26:21','2013-07-18 13:26:21','','shower','','inherit','open','open','','shower','','','2013-07-18 09:26:21','2013-07-18 13:26:21','',0,'http://mrcornelius.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/shower.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(513,3,'2014-05-01 10:06:14','2014-05-01 14:06:14','<a href=\"http://mrcornelius.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/gun_woman.jpg\"><img src=\"http://mrcornelius.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/gun_woman.jpg\" alt=\"gun_woman\" width=\"350\" height=\"258\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-514\" /></a>\r\n\r\nIt’s serendipitous. I swear, the planets must have aligned. How else do you explain all these states that have instituted ‘Stand Your Ground’ laws, AND have now made it perfectly legal to carry a gun into a bar?\r\nI mean, karma doesn’t get any better than this, does it ladies?\r\nFor you guys who aren’t putting this together yet, let me explain. You have NO IDEA what fear and intimidation is: there’s a black kid in your neighborhood? Someone is playing their music too loud? Puh-leeze.\r\nThink about a woman who leaves a bar and some drunk follows her to her car. Or she stays late at work and has to walk to the parking lot alone. Or leaves the mall after dark.  You clowns don’t have a clue.\r\nBut whatever the situation, our troubles are over, ladies! We’re free to pack heat and stand our ground.\r\nAccording to Georgia law, I have ‘No duty to retreat prior to use of force in self-defense (from) a person who uses threats or force, in accordance with Code Section 16-3-21.\r\nIn Michigan, an individual ‘may use deadly force against another individual anywhere he/she has the legal right to be with no duty to retreat if . . . [t]he individual honestly and reasonably believes that the use of deadly force is necessary to prevent the imminent death, great bodily harm, or sexual assault of himself or another individual.”\r\nWhoa! What? Did that say prevent sexual assault of himself? (Isn’t that just like a man to be more concerned that he might be assaulted by another guy? Let’s just add ‘herself’ to the mix, shall we?)\r\nThe bottom line is, if I honestly and reasonably believe a man intends to do me great bodily harm, I have every right to pull out my gun and shoot.\r\nSo fellas? The next time you hover too close to me, grab your crotch, and ask if I’d like some of what you got? You better think twice. Cause I’m packin’.\r\n','Are You Ready to Stand Your Ground, Ladies?','','publish','open','open','','ready-stand-ground-ladies','','','2014-05-01 10:06:14','2014-05-01 14:06:14','',0,'http://mrcornelius.com/?p=513',0,'post','',0),(514,3,'2014-05-01 10:01:58','2014-05-01 14:01:58','','gun_woman','','inherit','open','open','','gun_woman','','','2014-05-01 10:01:58','2014-05-01 14:01:58','',513,'http://mrcornelius.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/gun_woman.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(521,1,'2014-07-16 18:15:29','2014-07-16 22:15:29','<a href=\"http://mrcornelius.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/Habits_Kick_Back_Cover_for_Kindle.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-522\" src=\"http://mrcornelius.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/Habits_Kick_Back_Cover_for_Kindle-400x600.jpg\" alt=\"Habits Kick Back\" width=\"400\" height=\"600\" /></a>Prescription drugs are so common in the future they’re called supplements, and dispensed at meals like side dishes. Just like everyone else, Luna takes pills to curb her appetite, increase her memory, focus her concentration, improve her mood, even suppress her sex drive.\r\n\r\nBy her sophomore year in college, however, she’s beginning to wonder what life is like outside this drug-induced state. The perfect opportunity to break out of the mire comes when she sees a picture of a medallion from the 5<sup>th</sup> century. She’s not sure where she’s seen it, but she hopes once her mind is clear, she will find the artifact.\r\n\r\nWhen she stops taking supplements, she discovers food tastes delicious, her friend Sal is suddenly sexy, and the search for the lost medallion turns into a real adventure.\r\n\r\nHopefully, all her new habits don’t get her killed.\r\n<form action=\"https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr\" method=\"post\" target=\"_top\">\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"cmd\" value=\"_s-xclick\">\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"hosted_button_id\" value=\"7QWDQRRV7M7BU\">\r\n\r\n<a class=\"btn habits\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Habits-Kick-Back-Marsha-Cornelius-ebook/dp/B00LILUUT6/ref=asap_bc?ie=UTF8\" target=\"_blank\">Buy on Amazon</a>\r\n\r\n<span class=\"btnCaption habitCaption\">To purchase a signed a signed copy of this paperback.</span>\r\n<input formtarget=\"_blank\" type=\"image\" style= \"padding-top: 10px; margin-left: 125px;\" src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/btn/btn_buynowCC_LG.gif\" border=\"0\" name=\"submit\" alt=\"PayPal - The safer, easier way to pay online!\">\r\n<img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/scr/pixel.gif\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\">\r\n</form>\r\n','Habits Kick Back','','publish','open','open','','habits-kick-back-m-r-cornelius','','','2016-02-11 21:30:07','2016-02-12 02:30:07','',0,'http://mrcornelius.com/?p=521',0,'post','',0),(522,1,'2014-07-16 18:13:47','2014-07-16 22:13:47','','Habits Kick Back','','inherit','open','open','','habits_kick_back_cover_for_kindle','','','2014-07-16 18:13:47','2014-07-16 22:13:47','',521,'http://mrcornelius.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/Habits_Kick_Back_Cover_for_Kindle.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(528,3,'2016-01-25 16:31:28','2016-01-25 21:31:28','Do you have an idea for a book but don’t know how to start?\r\nHave you written the first chapter of your novel seven times and still don’t know how it ends??<a href=\"http://mrcornelius.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/clip-art-computers-079548.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-529\" src=\"http://mrcornelius.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/clip-art-computers-079548-400x332.jpg\" alt=\"clip-art-computers-079548\" width=\"169\" height=\"154\" /></a>\r\nAre there unfinished stories sitting in your computer?\r\n<em><strong> IT’S TIME TO GET SERIOUS</strong></em>\r\nYou know how a personal trainer meets with you weekly, puts you through an intensive workout and reviews your progress? Their job is to make you squat deeper and get your heart rate up higher so you can reach your goal.\r\nHow about Weight Watchers? The enormous success of this organization is due to its motivational leaders who offer suggestions, encouragement, and mentoring, while always cheering ‘Don’t give up!’\r\n<em><strong>YOU NEED SOMEONE LIKE THAT: A WRITING COACH</strong></em>\r\nI can be your personal trainer, your motivational leader who helps to get that book done. Here’s how it works: You submit pages the day before (if any), select a time that’s good for you, and together we discuss your work. Don’t have any pages done? Then let’s talk about what’s blocking your progress.\r\nGet help with:\r\n* Theme * Opening image * Set-up\r\n* Catalyst * Plot points * B story\r\n* Final scene * Protagonist * Antagonist\r\n* Dialogue * Narrative * Point of view\r\n* Outlining * Research * Rewriting\r\nMy job is to keep you moving forward to your goal: a completed manuscript\r\n\r\n<em><strong>DOES THIS SOUND FAMILIAR?</strong></em>\r\nYou’re in a critique group that also includes a short story writer, a poet, and a non-fiction essayist who are all struggling just like you. How can you get any meaningful feedback when the group only spends 5 to 10 minutes on your project?\r\nYour spouse/partner/friends don’t understand how difficult—and lonely—writing can be.\r\nYour mother is very supportive, but she doesn’t have a clue where your first plot point should be.\r\n<em><strong>DEFINITELY SOUNDS LIKE YOU NEED A WRITING COACH</strong></em>\r\nServices offered:\r\n* Weekly, bi-weekly, or monthly consults\r\n* One-time confab\r\n* Developmental read-through of completed manuscript available\r\n\r\nEmail me at <em><strong>marsha.cornelius@hotmail.com</strong></em> for more info and quotes.','LET’S FINISH THAT BOOK!','','publish','open','open','','lets-finish-book','','','2016-01-25 16:44:57','2016-01-25 21:44:57','',0,'http://mrcornelius.com/?p=528',0,'post','',0),(529,3,'2015-08-26 17:41:45','2015-08-26 21:41:45','','clip-art-computers-079548','','inherit','open','open','','clip-art-computers-079548','','','2015-08-26 17:41:45','2015-08-26 21:41:45','',528,'http://mrcornelius.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/clip-art-computers-079548.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(530,3,'2015-08-26 17:42:03','2015-08-26 21:42:03','','images','','inherit','open','open','','images','','','2015-08-26 17:42:03','2015-08-26 21:42:03','',528,'http://mrcornelius.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/images.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(531,3,'2015-08-26 17:42:13','2015-08-26 21:42:13','','images (1)','','inherit','open','open','','images-1','','','2015-08-26 17:42:13','2015-08-26 21:42:13','',528,'http://mrcornelius.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/images-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(533,3,'2015-08-30 12:46:53','2015-08-30 16:46:53','','Writing coach','','inherit','open','open','','writing-coach','','','2015-08-30 12:46:53','2015-08-30 16:46:53','',0,'http://mrcornelius.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Writing-coach.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(541,3,'2015-09-10 20:12:53','2015-09-11 00:12:53','<div class=\"coachPage\">\r\n[one_half]<h1><span><strong>LET’S FINISH THAT BOOK!</strong></span></h1>\r\nDo you have an idea for a book but don’t know how to start?\r\n\r\nHave you written the first chapter of your novel seven times and still don’t know how it ends?\r\n\r\nAre there unfinished stories sitting in your computer?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><span><strong>IT’S TIME TO GET SERIOUS</strong></span></h3>\r\nPersonal trainers meet with clients to develop a fitness regimen and a workout schedule, then they meet weekly to review the client\'s progress.\r\n\r\nCareer transition companies employ coaches who work with clients to update their resumes, teach them how to interview, and stick with them every step of the way to that new job.\r\n\r\nHow about Weight Watchers? The enormous success of this organization is due to its motivational leaders who offer suggestions, encouragement, and mentoring, while always cheering ‘Don’t give up!’[/one_half]\r\n[one_half_last]<img src=\"http://mrcornelius.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/pexels-photo.jpg\" alt=\"writing\" />[/one_half_last]\r\n\r\n<h3><span><strong>YOU NEED SOMEONE LIKE THAT: A WRITING COACH</strong></span></h3>\r\nI\'ll be your personal trainer, your motivational leader, the coach who will help you get that book done.\r\n\r\nHere’s how it works: You submit pages (if any), select a time that’s good for you, and together we discuss your work. \r\nDon’t have any pages done? Then let’s talk about what’s blocking your progress.\r\n\r\nGet help with:\r\n[one_third]* Theme \r\n* Catalyst \r\n* Final scene \r\n* Dialogue \r\n* Outlining[/one_third][one_third]* Opening image\r\n* Plot points\r\n* Protagonist\r\n* Narrative\r\n* Research[/one_third][one_third_last]\r\n* Set-up\r\n* B story\r\n* Antagonist\r\n* Point of view\r\n* Rewriting[/one_third_last]\r\n                                                                           \r\n<strong><em>My job is to keep you moving forward to your goal: a completed manuscript</em></strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>DOES THIS SOUND FAMILIAR?</strong>\r\n\r\nYou’re in a critique group with a short story writer, a poet, and a non-fiction essayist who are all struggling just like you. \r\nHow can you get any meaningful feedback when the group only spends 5 to 10 minutes on your project?\r\n\r\nYour spouse/partner/friends don’t understand how difficult—and lonely—writing can be.\r\n\r\nYour mother is very supportive, but she doesn’t have a clue where your first plot point should be.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><span><strong>DEFINITELY SOUNDS LIKE YOU NEED A WRITING COACH\r\n</strong></span></h3>\r\n<strong>\r\nServices offered:</strong>\r\n\r\n* Weekly, bi-weekly, or monthly consults\r\n\r\n* One-time confab\r\n\r\n* Developmental read-through of completed manuscript available\r\n<em>Email me at </em><a href=\"mailto:marsha.cornelius@hotmail.com\"><em>marsha.cornelius@hotmail.com</em></a><em> for more info and quotes.</em>\r\n</div>','Writing Coach','','publish','open','open','','services','','','2017-07-19 10:14:42','2017-07-19 14:14:42','',0,'http://mrcornelius.com/?page_id=541',0,'page','',0),(545,3,'2015-09-10 20:18:31','2015-09-11 00:18:31','','Picture1','','inherit','open','open','','picture1','','','2015-09-10 20:18:31','2015-09-11 00:18:31','',541,'http://mrcornelius.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Picture1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(547,3,'2015-09-10 20:24:03','2015-09-11 00:24:03','','Picture2','','inherit','open','open','','picture2','','','2015-09-10 20:24:03','2015-09-11 00:24:03','',541,'http://mrcornelius.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Picture2.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(549,3,'2015-09-10 20:27:17','2015-09-11 00:27:17',' ','','','publish','open','closed','','549','','','2017-07-19 09:12:22','2017-07-19 13:12:22','',0,'http://mrcornelius.com/?p=549',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(551,3,'2015-09-10 20:40:51','2015-09-11 00:40:51','','Picture3','','inherit','open','open','','picture3','','','2015-09-10 20:40:51','2015-09-11 00:40:51','',541,'http://mrcornelius.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Picture3.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(562,3,'2015-10-27 15:05:51','2015-10-27 19:05:51','Everyone has advice on ways to stay healthy. I\'m supposed to eat kale, and huff turmeric. I can eat any old potatoes but nothing other than organic strawberries. No more bacon? Puh-leeze. I walk every day, but now I find out I\'m supposed to do this at different speeds to keep my body confused.\r\n\r\nWell you know what? I\'m confused by all these recommendations I\'ve seen lately. How am I supposed to do all the suggested bending, and tapping, and pulling, and twisting?\r\n\r\nHere’s a hypothetical look at what my day could look like.\r\n<h2><strong>MORNING</strong></h2>\r\nThis could be an absolute nightmare because of all the time involved.\r\n<h4><em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>TOP 3</strong> </span></em></h4>\r\nThese are exercises to do before I get out of bed. Now right away I see trouble, because when I stretch my arms over my head, I’m going to hit the headboard, and knock over my glass of water. (Scoot, scoot, scoot.) Okay, I’m in the middle of the bed, but now the woman in the video wants me to pull my knees in and twist to the side. But wait a minute. She’s gripping the sides of the exercise board she’s using. What am I supposed to grip? Hubby’s leg? The cat’s tail?\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/U-ztuWEHu5c\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>CAT/COW</strong></span></em></h4>\r\nMy yoga instructor says that doing the cat/cow move once I’m out of bed is a good way to warm up and get the circulation going in my back. I decided if I\'m going to get down on my rickety knees first thing in the morning, I might as well see if there are any other moves. I found these simple exercises to get me on my way to a happy and productive day.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/7-Zgus9Cy8M\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n <em>Child’s pose</em> – that’s easy. And there is<em> cat/cow</em>. Looks like I’m on the right track. <em>Down dog</em> is simple enough, but then it gets a bit more complicated when she wants me to bring my knee to my nose. When I see her do it, I think ‘Geez, don’t smack yourself in the face.’ But of course, I’m never going to get my knee even close to my nose, so yeah, I can do this.\r\n\r\nOh, now she’s just getting ridiculous. She wants me to balance in a <em>crescent lunge</em>, and then bend from side to side? Does she know how old I am??\r\n<h4><em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>PULLING</strong></span></em></h4>\r\nOkay I’m all limber, and thinking positive thoughts, I’ve got my mojo workin’. But what about internally? What about all those toxins, and all that wine I drank last night. If I get a tablespoon of coconut oil and swish it around in my mouth for 20 minutes, I can cleanse internally.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/pfGrgDJn18Q\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n So before I brush my teeth, or eat or drink anything I need to ‘pull’ for 20 minutes. Now I don\'t know about your coconut oil, but mine looks more like Crisco. So am I supposed to let it melt in my mouth? Ewww. One website suggested melting it first. And hopefully it will get runnier than the gloppy spoonful this woman pops in her mouth. And for God’s sake don’t spit that crap out in the sink or you’ll be calling a plumber. And then you\'ll be hanging around at home during the 8 – 12 time slot. (And we all know he\'s not going to arrive until 11:49.)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>NOON</strong></h2>\r\nI sit at a computer for long periods, so I try to take breaks every 20 minutes to stretch and walk around. But these are only temporary fixes. By lunch time, my back is usually screaming. (Please don\'t tell me I\'ve got the wrong chair, because for what hubby paid for this monstrosity, it\'s going to be in the family for a VERY long time.)\r\n<h4><em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>TAPPING</strong></span></em></h4>\r\nWhen I heard about tapping, I decided this was the answer to my prayers. Since my back pain is really just tension in the muscles, I figured I could psyche the pain away. As I tap the first pressure point, (the karate chop point) I repeat my mantra ‘Although my back is killing me, I accept myself and how I feel.’\r\n\r\nThen I move on to the other pressure points while I vent. Tap, tap, tap . . . ‘I’m feeling all this pain’, tap, tap, tap ‘All this pain is frustrating.’ tap, tap, tap . . . ‘will this fricking pain stop or should I go lie down and watch Ellen?’\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/J6yzIez29Ms\" width=\"420\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\nI have a 50/50 chance that after enough rounds of tapping, I can get back to writing. Or at least with all that deep breathing, and affirming what a great person I am, I have temporarily forgotten about my pain.  But now I’m blocked. I can’t think of how to end the chapter I\'m working on. This is when I need . . . TA-DA!\r\n<h4><em><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">SUPER BRAIN YOGA</span></strong></em></h4>\r\nAccording to the report, this is like calisthenics for the brain. Doctors recommend it for seniors, people with Alzheimers, kids in classrooms, even autistic kids. Everyone benefits from stimulating the brain.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/KSwhpF9iJSs\" width=\"420\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Grasping an earlobe in each hand, I squat and breathe. Breathe and squat. It’s only for 3 minutes, so surely I can work this into my schedule. The exercise helps my back, and the ear-lobe pulling is going to make me a genius in no time. (I find that watching cute cat videos helps me pass the time.)</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>AND NIGHT</strong></h2>\r\nAlthough I don’t keep my bedroom too hot, or watch TV, or eat a heavy meal, I have a terrible time sleeping. I blame my kids for this. For five years I was awakened 2 to 3 times a night for feedings, and that’s how often I wake up now. Coincidence? I think not.\r\n\r\nI sip my Sleepytime tea while reading, I take my melatonin an hour before bedtime, and I NEVER drink. (Well, sometimes I replace the tea with a glass of wine, but I swear it’s only one small glass.)\r\n<h4><em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>RELAXATION</strong></span></em></h4>\r\nI decided that if exercising in the morning is a good idea, maybe I should do it at night, too.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/YwAqlgkdGEA\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFirst of all, I will NEVER be able to watch this video before I go to bed because the woman’s voice is soooo grating. Better to just jot everything down and keep it on the headboard with my water.\r\n\r\n<em>Child’s Pose</em> – yep, did that this morning. And it is definitely a relaxing position. I begin to clear my thoughts.\r\n\r\n<em>Seated Forward Bend</em> – Oh, yeah, that feels good on the old back.\r\n\r\n<em>Butterfly pose</em> – stimulates and activates your second chakra which is related to your sexual and reproductive . . . wait! WHAT? I’m trying to go to sleep here.\r\n\r\n<em>Happy baby</em> – hold for 30 seconds. Oh, right. As soon as hubby sees this, he’s going to be all ‘yeah, I’ll make you my happy baby.’ Which is when I head immediately into—\r\n\r\n<em>Corpse pose</em> – I\'ll play dead for as long as it takes for him to either turn on a football game, or roll over and go to sleep.','FIT BIT(CH)','','publish','open','open','','fit-bitch','','','2015-10-27 15:05:51','2015-10-27 19:05:51','',0,'http://mrcornelius.com/?p=562',0,'post','',2),(583,3,'2015-12-25 19:19:50','2015-12-26 00:19:50','<h2></h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://mrcornelius.com/2015/25/tale-moral-corruption/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-257\"><img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-257\" title=\"a tale of moral corruption\" src=\"http://mrcornelius.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/the-corruption-kindle.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"220\" height=\"330\" /></a><em><strong>How does a man plummet into a world of male escorts, kinky sex, and death matches? </strong></em>\r\n\r\nMason can’t wait to be a loving father and supportive husband. He’s especially looking forward to wearing the new artificial womb that so many men have strapped on their bellies. But first, he must be chosen from the Approved Partner Registry, a website that profiles men and their qualifications. It’s used by businesswomen who don’t have the time or inclination to date. When he is dropped from the registry, his life begins to unravel and it doesn’t look like anything can stop his fall from grace.\r\n\r\n<a class=\"btn taleBtn\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Tale-Moral-Corruption-Marsha-Cornelius-ebook/dp/B018YNIUU6/ref=asap_bc?ie=UTF8\" target=\"_blank\">Buy on